# Notes
# -----
# - `note: skipped:disabled` refers to the LLM classifier (llm.enabled=false in
#   this run). The rules detector did fire — see `det_rules`.
# - `det_latency_ms: 0` reflects the resolution of perf_counter()→int(ms); the
#   actual time was sub-millisecond.
# - The `raw` column ALWAYS contains the original bytes (forensics, ADR-0004
#   §5). Only the bytes leaving the proxy are replaced.
# - Correlation: the `trace=219fbc09` in the replacement text is a sha1 prefix
#   of the original line + nano-timestamp. To find this audit row from a user
#   report, search the events table for that text in the raw column or look
#   the row up by id.
